# Architecture Flow Diagram & Breakdown

Below is the complete end-to-end flow diagram illustrating the fortified architecture. It maps out the exact sequence of events, including the resilience mechanisms (Reaper, GC, and Locking) and the hand-off between the orchestrator and the processing pod using the shared PVC.

## 1. Flow Diagram (Mermaid)

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph OpenShift Cluster
        Trigger((Cron Schedule))
        
        subgraph Orchestrator
            Orch[s3-import-job Pod]
            Reaper{1. Reaper Mechanism}
            GC{2. PVC Garbage Collection}
            Lock{3. Pessimistic Lock Check}
            Fabric8[4. Fabric8 API Launcher]
        end
        
        subgraph Batch Processor
            Processor[file-processing-job Pod]
            Batch[Spring Batch Execution]
            Cleanup[5. PVC File Cleanup]
        end

        PVC[(ReadWriteMany PVC: /mnt/moss-data)]
    end

    subgraph AWS
        S3_IN[S3: input/]
        S3_PROC[S3: in-process/]
        S3_DONE[S3: success/ or failed/]
    end
    
    subgraph Database
        DB[(PostgreSQL)]
    end

    %% --- Orchestrator Flow ---
    Trigger -->|Fires| Orch
    Orch --> Reaper
    Reaper -->|Fails records >2 hrs| DB
    Reaper --> GC
    GC -->|Deletes orphaned files| PVC
    GC --> Lock
    Lock -->|Checks for PROCESSING state| DB
    
    Lock -- If Locked --> Exit([Exit Gracefully])
    Lock -- If Clear --> Fetch
    
    Fetch[List Oldest File] --> S3_IN
    Fetch -->|Downloads File| PVC
    Fetch -->|Inserts PROCESSING record| DB
    Fetch -->|Moves File| S3_PROC
    Fetch --> Fabric8
    
    %% --- Hand-off ---
    Fabric8 -.->|Submits dynamic Job YAML| Processor

    %% --- Processor Flow ---
    Processor --> Batch
    Batch -->|Reads file locally| PVC
    Batch -.->|Chunk Processing State| DB
    
    Batch -->|On Completion| UpdateDB[Update DB Status]
    UpdateDB --> DB
    UpdateDB -->|Moves File| S3_DONE
    
    UpdateDB --> Cleanup
    Cleanup -->|Deletes physical file| PVC
    Cleanup --> Terminate([Pod Terminates])
